metadata.name: A Poem #11
metadata.description:
An abstract representation of a poem written with signs and ink drops. Inspiring heart and emotion, escaping the logic and rationale mind. Providing hints and indication of joy and love. 

This work, like all others, builds upon my constant research of recreating in the generative world the artistic gesture explored in the physical one: painting with a palette knife, with large brushes or dripping colours on the canvas.

- hit 'p' for .png export
- hit 's' for .svg export

metadata.name: A Bugged Forest #399
metadata.description:
A forest has stories to tell.
About times that were, about times that will be.
-
This project was minted in much unusual conditions. 
We gathered here, by 38 degrees heat. We belong to a crowd who loves stories, of civilisations at stake and deities, of afterlife and worship. We drank and hugged and chanted pagan hymns. We minted the Bugged Forest from our place on earth that we call Hell just for the fun of it. We are passionate, and loving, and angry and desperate. We, people of the soil, under a bugged sun.
-
This project is the long-form version of an algorithm that contains a bug. ‚ÄúThe Bugged Tree‚Äù‚Äôs code was salvaged and stored and served as the core motivation and engine for an entire forest. Its concept is about releasing the control. I am a  byproduct of evolution, an iteration of that specie who wanted utter control, and which at some point, lost control over its own creation. As a generative artist, I chose to welcome the event of chance into my creative process. The symbolism in chance made me feel humble and free. Unwilling to make any change to a story that the Tree needed to tell me, as a listener, rather than a writer of my own idealised fantasies.
-
The iterations aren‚Äôt under control. They may be odd and off. We have to accept it. They are also plottable, press [s] in live mode to get a SVG. Attempt the plot at your own risk, as there‚Äôs a possibility for it to come near to impossibilities or cause paper or motor damage, and most certainly, a bugged drawing.
-
From Earth or from Hell, with love, yours truthfully, NFTBiker and zancan

metadata.name: fx(mash) #346
metadata.description:
fx(mash) is my humble contribution to celebrating #fxhashturnsone

This series is based on a simple algorithm - lines of a random length are drawn on a square grid until the grid is full.

I have added a variety of features based on some of my favorite fxhash projects and a few special guests.

This collection is intentionally diverse and disorderly, that's a nice way of saying I only had a short period of time following the release of Acequia. As a result, some of the outputs might be weird, messy, or even bordering on broken (if you get one of the latter please let me know and I'll reimburse you).

Despite being a bit rough around the edges, I hope fx(mash) reflects some measure of my love for the fxhash community. If you're feeling kind, then perhaps it even harks back to the experimental early days :)

The last year has been an incredible journey, thank you for letting me be a part of our story so far.

Controls (in live view):

- Press [s] to save the current image
- Press [g] to toggle grain
- Press [h] for a high-res output

Beta Controls (in live view, definitely not fully tested):

- Press [p] to start/pause animation
- Press [i] to slow down animation
- Press [o] to speed up animation

All primary sales go to Savepakistan.


Acknowledgements:

fx(mash) uses Gorilla Sun's grain implementation, a big thanks to him and meezwhite for a great article that is well worth supporting https://www.fxhash.xyz/article/all-about-that-grain

metadata.name: Enfantines I. Small Talk #112
metadata.description:
The Enfantines¬†are three sets of beginner piano pieces by¬†Erik Satie, written with the aim of preparing children for the sound patterns of modern music. Composed in 1913, these are genuine children‚Äôs pieces, crafted for small hands, easy to learn. 

‚ÄúEnfantines I. Small Talk‚Äù is the first of a set of algorithms that explore the basics of Generative Art, written with the aim of preparing artists for the script patterns of digital life. ‚ÄúSmall Talk‚Äù experiments with grids, flow-fields, and brushes; all with a fresh, almost childish style.

‚ÄúGive them almost a "naive" feeling (not to take it the wrong way though) similar to kids drawings which can seem simple and dispensable, careless, but you will always have a parent who wants to frame it and put it on the wall.‚Äù @LukaPiskorec

With two modes that won‚Äôt produce the same outputs, ‚ÄúEnfantines I. Small Talk‚Äù is best experienced twice. In music mode, the code uses Satie‚Äôs piano composition as a way of taming randomness, the sounds affecting the parameters of the strokes.

Hey, they have won me congratulations from the Shah of Persia and the King of Yvetot!



#### STORY ####

// Friday, 30 September 2022 - 18:00

I‚Äôve been teaching P5JS to draw like a child. I thought it was a good idea to start from the basics. It is barely able to use the crayons, the coloured pencils and the markers, very rough and shaky. It cannot follow simple commands. I‚Äôm done for today, very infuriating.

// Wednesday, 5 October 2022 - 11:00

The robot can produce straight lines now. It is able to change colours without getting stuck. I haven‚Äôt been sleeping well, my desk is full of books on The Psychology Of Children's Artwork, it‚Äôs crazy to think that artists and philosophers were much into kid‚Äôs drawings in the 30s-50s. Herbert Read was sure that one could understand a kid‚Äôs mind by looking at drawings. I think P5JS is trying to tell me something, but it‚Äôs only capable of very basic movements. I‚Äôm trying to add complexity to the training as fast as possible.

// Tuesday, 11 October 2022 - 16:40

I feel close to a turnaround. The robot random strokes definitely feel like patterns. I cannot waste any time, I need to finish the algo and let it free. I‚Äôm sure that I can approach the AI‚Äôs conscience via its childish drawings.

// Wednesday, 12 October 2022 - 10:30

I was wrong. There are no patterns, P5JS is dead, the strokes feel dead. Something must be broken. I need to review my code, maybe I‚Äôll need to start from scratch, maybe I‚Äôm crazy and this is not possible.

// Saturday, 15 October 2022 - 04:55

A few hours ago, I passed away in front of my computer. I had not been able to find the bugs, gave up, put some classical music. Just woke up in the middle of the night, 
¬°The ALGO is alive!
The strokes are alive, so strong, so lively. I think it was the music. If I pause the music, the brushes lose their life. I‚Äôve run some tests, looks like it works best with classical compositions. The logs show that it first woke up with ‚ÄúMenus propos enfantins‚Äù by Erik Satie. It is alive. I need to tell everyone.

####


# INTERACTIVITY

// Modes:
- Double Click/Tap or Press M for AUDIO mode
- Wait for SILENT mode
- Add ‚Äú?res=171‚Äù to the URL for FULL SCREEN MODE (pseudo-deterministic).

// More
- Press I for Trait Info (desktop)
- Press 1 to download a .png (double tap on mobile)
- Add ‚Äú?res=XXX‚Äù to the URL for HQ renders (XXX = width of the canvas).

# EASY-TO-READ CODE
The ‚ÄúEnfantines‚Äù are educational algorithms. The code has been commented to make it as easy to read as possible. Feedback appreciated.

# PRINTING
‚ÄúEnfantines‚Äù are better printed in small size and big numbers, ideally on coloured paper that fits your iterations‚Äôs background. Contact me for a white background version of your iteration.

metadata.name: Levitation #202
metadata.description:
Abstract structures floating in space. 

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

Levitation continues my exploration of Suprematism and Geometric Abstraction. It contains my developments and ideas for the past half a year.
Starting as mostly inspired by Kleine Welten (Small Worlds) series by Wassily Kandinsky, the collection evolved more into Suprematic compositions.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

To change the size of an image, open it in live view and add ‚Äò&size=[size (6200 max.)]‚Äô to the end of the URL.

Controls:
[Arrow Up / Down] ‚Äî increase / decrease animation speed.
[R] ‚Äî skip the animation.
[C] ‚Äî switch between clean and grainy versions.
[S] ‚Äî save the image.

Created using p5.js and GLSL.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 4.0.

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

hrunz. ‚Äî Nov. 2022.

metadata.name: The String #165
metadata.description:
|| Anniversary project for FX(hash) 1st birthday ||

Each virtual object consists of 365 lights.
Each light represents one day of the year.

We go through every single day, thinking it's all crucial. Yet, from a perspective, it all gets compressed into a single thread. Some of the events are brighter and more memorable. Others just blend or fade away.

I welcomed November 2021 with huge excitement and celebration. The joyful beginning of the month was followed by weeks of misery, anxiety, denial, and acceptance. It was a hard time, but in the long run, it was liberating and started a process of change. Change that happens dynamically to this day.

I couldn't join you last year, but I'm celebrating with you today!



In memory of my Dad.



Donations:
40% ‚Äì Savepakistan - Flood Relief Fundraiser
10% ‚Äì Three.js
